With 24+ years of IT experience and a current AI Engineer Bootcamp and IBM Generative AI Engineering certification under my belt, I bring something most AI candidates lack: proven reliability engineering discipline built on real production systems at scale.

At USDA, I engineered performance and reliability frameworks that increased system throughput by 40% and reduced defect resolution time by 35%, while maintaining SLA compliance of under five seconds per transaction across high-volume environments. I scaled systems to 12,000+ transactions per minute at Sprint/CenturyLink and leveraged an enterprise observability stack — AppDynamics, Splunk, Prometheus, and Grafana — that maps directly to monitoring AI model inference latency, throughput, and reliability in production.

Testing AI APIs and model endpoints is fundamentally the same discipline as load testing distributed web services. I bring that performance engineering rigor to AI reliability from day one.

I am fully remote-ready and available immediately. I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my background aligns with LiveMindz's AI Reliability Engineering needs.

